//@version=6
// ts_screener — a compact trend flag for scanning a watchlist/screener.
// Same dual-EMA logic (PARITY). Plots +1 (uptrend), -1 (downtrend), 0 (flat) so you can
// add it to several symbols and eyeball which are trending, or use it in a Pine-screener
// style scan. No orders, no alerts by default.
//
// Manual: surface candidate setups across many symbols, then open the playbook on the best.
// Bot: a pre-filter — only arm ts_trend_strategy on symbols the screener flags trending.
indicator("TS Screener (trend flag)", overlay=false)

fast      = input.int(20, "Fast EMA")
slow      = input.int(50, "Slow EMA")
atrPeriod = input.int(14, "ATR period")

emaFast = ta.ema(close, fast)
emaSlow = ta.ema(close, slow)
atrVal  = ta.atr(atrPeriod)
warmedUp = bar_index >= math.max(slow, atrPeriod + 1)

flag = not warmedUp ? 0 : emaFast > emaSlow ? 1 : emaFast < emaSlow ? -1 : 0
volatile = (atrVal / close) > 0.01

plot(flag, "Trend flag", color = flag > 0 ? color.green : flag < 0 ? color.red : color.gray,
     style = plot.style_columns)
hline(0, "flat", color.new(color.gray, 60))

// Optional: only flag "tradeable" trends (directional AND volatile).
plotchar(flag != 0 and volatile, "tradeable", "•", location.top,
         color = flag > 0 ? color.green : color.red)
